Title: My Brain is a Race Car
Review: We love this book! It is exactly what I've been looking for. I read the first two pages and watched my son's ears perk up as he quieted his singing and his action figures. He said, "that's like me!" and I knew I had found a way to help him understand his world a little bit better. Thank you for this. It is beautiful. We love the art. And it just means the world to us to have resources for kids his age.

Title: My Brain is a Race Car
Review: Simply amazing. The book is so very well written, it made me teary on the first read. I love that it gave us some inspiration to work out what our own pit stops might look like. From the bottom of my heart, thank you for writing this book!

Title: 8 Reading Logs for Kids Printable/ Instant Download / Reading Chart / Reading Logs / Struggling Readers / Log Templates / Printable Log
Review:
LOVE, LOVE, LOVE! We've added this to our homeschool and it's be wonderful, though I'm confident it would be great for any child, home schooled, private, public ect...

Our oldest is an avid reader and I've noticed I'm spending less time reading to our little ones since she started reading to them as part of her daily work. This pack has encourage us all to read more. 

8 different charting/log options should fit any range of reading from picture books read aloud with a spot to color for each day read - all the way to the independent reader to keep track of titles, time and reactions to books. There are also great suggestions for successfully implementing each chart. 

Overall, if you're on the fence, get it. You won't regret it!

Title: Never, Never Quit Children's Book
Review: As a mom of three creative young girls this book brought me to tears. It is exactly the encouragement I want them to receive. On Christmas morning they actually stopped opening gifts to sit together and read it. They loved each page of illustrations, pointing out favorite characters and getting more and more excited. My oldest felt seen when we got to the part about the frustration that can come from not being able to create what you are envisioning in your head. I'm so grateful this book was written. No doubt the next generation of artists is already being inspired by it.

Title: Children's book - Tukoni Picture Book - Book for Kids - Badtime Stories - Animal Book - Forest Book - Children's literature
Review: I found this artist primarily because I wanted to give money directly to the little businesses  of Ukraine during this awful war.  I love beautiful illustrations for books, we have a ton of grandkids, we live in a forest, and her work fit our need perfectly! But OH. MY. GOSH. I was so overwhelmed with the quality and care that this artist puts into her work! The books are amazingly GORGEOUS! Now I am on the hunt for some of her harder to get books to add to my Grands library. These books are big, beautiful, and thought provoking. My babies LOVE them! I love exposing them to a different language and I have carefully printed a translation on each page for my older Grands to enjoy reading. Thank you for such a gem! And God bless and keep you safe.

Review: I absolutely love this book.  It is beautiful inside and out. The words are stunning.  I was thrown off by the customer service tho.  I reached out to let them know the note I know I added was not sent.  I know I wrote a note in the proper space and clicked this is a gift.  The note was very personal and took me a few minutes to write.  I wanted to let the owner know just in case there was an internal issue.  I wasn’t complaining, or upset just wanted make them aware.  The response summarized was, no you did not write a note.  Which I did and why I was following up. And then basically told to take it up with Etsy as that’s their system.  Being that it is someone’s company you would think they would want to check on that themselves as this is their business.  Was just a little surprised.

I noticed the text has changed slightly. I only noticed because I had memorized the book and found myself reciting the last version. Finding board books in Western Armenian are hard Im glad I found such a great one.

Title: Educational Picture Book for Children -- PERSONALIZED children's book -- homeschool Learning book -- personalized book for kids kindergarten
Review:
What Will Grow is a charming and gorgeous book. Jennifer Ward is the author, and Susie Ghahremani is the talented illustrator. Every inch of this book is a pleasure to view.  

All my sons love Susie Ghahremani's artwork. They love her soothing colors, whimsical characters, the happiness that her work inspires. I, myself, love opening my new little books and just feasting my senses. I am often heartsick at the hate in our world.  This sounds a bit too deep for a review, but it's true...Susie's work allows me to view something that brings my soul some peace, and inspires me to make life more bright and beautiful for others.

Title: Combo: Book of Mormon Vol 1 & 2
Review: The product itself is great! However, when I purchased the books I didn't realize there would be sooo much work and extra cost involved in creating the final product. If you want a book that looks like the picture, you will need to: color copy each page onto white cardstock (there are about 24 pages per book), laminate those pages, and then spiral bind the book. You may also need velcro dots or sticky tack to adhere different pieces to activity pages. Finally, there are a few pages that would require an expo marker. Overall, the books are darling and my kids will love them. Just pricier than I expected with all the extra costs added in! The videos are super helpful. I should have watched those first before purchasing.

Title: The Everyday Mother Mini - Ivory Baby Tracking Log Book - Breastfeed log - Pumping Log
Review:
This is so much better than I even imagined. It’s everything to me and my newborn. NICU was a tough way to start her life for two weeks, and this book has helped us transition from formula bottles to breastfeeding. 

It’s my daily planner, reminder to shower and absolutely helps me not worry about ‘. Omg when did she last poop!?’ I can look back and see it all. 

Oh and ps- no safety pin or hair and for us. I just mark Left or Right on the left column to remember which breast to start at.

Review:
OK, seriously! This book is awesome, it’s a rare find that addresses challenges of creative individuality. What it is like to be that one kid that is bright with a love for Science, Physics and Art. That one kid that is sometimes misunderstood by their peers and yet through sheer determination and imagination comes out on top.
My granddaughters aged seven and 11 loved the story and thought the drawings were great. 
I’m Gram and I give this book a far beyond 5 golden ⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️

Title: Rocky's Big Christmas Adventure
Review: I have ordered the book Rocky's BIG Christmas Adventure: Based on a True Story by Janet Leigh Towell for my collection of children's books and for use in my classroom. This book exceeded my expectations. Every page is illustrated by this author. The pictures are very colorful, detailed, and cute. Some of these illustrations are just framable art for a baby room or a primary classroom. The story is captivating and, also, very informative. The language of this book is welcoming for a family member and a child to sit on a sofa and read together. This book will be a gem of my collection.
